6:
I think I overdid it a bit on today's
expedition... I'm beat. When we get
back, I'm making dinner first thing.
20:
I swear I heard a sound. A voice, and
maybe a monster?
28:
Gah, it's no use. No matter how
many times I try, it doesn't work!
35:
And I have no idea how to get back
to Landosol—what's going to
happen to Her Majesty?
45: Alk, we need to help her!
51:
What's the matter with you
monsters? You're supposed to listen
to me and do as I say!
57: Guess she didn't need any help.
63:
You guys—aren't you the ones from
before?
69:
Indeed. I believe the last time we
saw each other was in battle. I'm
glad to see you are hale and hearty.
74:
What brings you to a place like this?
Are you on a quest from the guild?
80:
N-no. I was... actually just practicing
my magic.
86: Oh, I see. Sorry to interrupt!
91:
We shall be going then. Until next
time, Karyl.
109:
The thing is... I have a favor to ask
you.
113:
Would you be able to escort me to
Palpebra?
122:
I uh... may or may not have gotten
lost while training out here.
130:
Sorry! I just thought it was going to
be something way more
serious—you should have seen the
look on your face.
135:
In that case, let us head back
together.
142:
It seems you've adjusted to life in
Palpebra after all. I'm glad to see it.
146:
I'm sure it hasn't been easy—aaand
we're here!
148:
Being engrossed in your training is
one thing, but make sure you do so
in moderation, all right?
151:
Have you thought about going to
the Academy? It costs a bit to get in,
but there's tons of useful facilities for
magic users like you!
156:
I don't really want to be seen. By
anyone. I'm working on a very...
special type of magic right now.
161:
This magic must be very important
to you.
165:
I learned it from a person very dear
to me. But I haven't been able to get
it to work ever since coming to
Palpebra...
168:
I mean, I wasn't particularly good at
using it before either, but now I can't
use it at all...
172:
Perhaps there's something we can
try.
178:
Wh-wh-what the heck was that?!
And where are we now?!
182:
Starview Village—a place at the
intersection of multiple worlds.
184:
Using the World Flipper, it's possible
to travel back and forth to many
different worlds.
186:
Perhaps if you try your magic on
different worlds, you may be
successful in one of them.
189:
Forget about that spell—I can use
this thing to get back to Landosol,
can't I?!
191:
It is possible. The World Flipper exists
on all worlds.
194:
On all worlds?! I wonder if Her
Majesty knew anything about this...
199:
As you can see, we might be able to
help you. Assuming you're willing, of
course.
203:
Company makes everything better,
right? Light here is trying to find his
way home too.
208:
Huh? You're on an important quest
like that, and you're wasting time
helping me out?! What's wrong with
you guys!
212:
It's no problem whatsoever. Besides,
having a powerful mage like you on
our side is to our advantage!
216:
You're certainly a generous and kind
bunch, huh.
220:
Fine! If that's the case, then I
suppose I'd be willing to lend you a
hand.
224:
We are happy to have you, Karyl.
Welcome to the team.
231: Um... thanks, I guess. For everything.
237:
Haha, so you do have an
affectionate side to you!
242:
What? No, I don't! Shut up! Keep
saying weird stuff like that, and I'll
shut you up permanently!
